{"type":"message","id":"21f2d93d","parentId":"388de156","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:57:34.766Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fm5ms7ei8251_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 145617\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE (Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec)\r\n3. CFI Compression Experiment COMPLETE - discovered that CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is too aggressive\r\n4. NEW INSIGHT: Constant Format Problem - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n5. SYNTHESIS: Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n\r\nThe NEXT EXPERIMENT is clear:\r\n- Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n- Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split\r\n\r\nThis is the concrete next action - implement and run this experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what files I need to create/modify:\r\n\r\n1. I need to create a script or experiment that implements the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Compare it against the binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n3. Run on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Create an experiment script that implements the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Run it against the pulse data\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pulse data - I have `pulse_2026-03-24 145515.md` as the last pulse. The experiment data should be in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`.\r\n\r\nLet me check what I can do concretely:\r\n\r\nOption 1: Create a new experiment script that implements the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\nOption 2: Update the existing experiment documentation with the new hypothesis to test\r\n\r\n\r\nOption 3: Create the experiment design document\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a structured experiment design that captures the key parameters and methodology. The script will need to parse pulse data, calculate the hybrid score, and compare performance against binary threshold approaches. I'll prioritize creating a modular experiment framework that allows for easy replication and extension of the current research direction.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Experiment identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts that look causal but carry zero information. The next step is to implement and test the hybrid scoring formula against binary thresholds.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a new experiment script `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` that implements Strategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120), with 80/20 train/test split on 200 pulses, comparing against the binary threshold approach.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe hybrid formula should:\r\n- De-weight constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.00 → score≈1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0, but freq/120=1.33 capped at 1.0)\r\n- Properly score research trajectory tokens (freq=60, CFI=0.7 → score=0.7 × 0.5 = 0.35)\r\n- Better distinguish signal from metaprogramming noise\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n- 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split\r\n- Strategy A: Binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n- Strategy C: Hybrid score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Metric: Precision, Recall, F1 for identifying \"important\" tokens\r\n\r\n## Pending\r\n- [ ] Implement scoring formulas\r\n- [ ] Run on pulse corpus\r\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall curves\r\nfile: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:56:32\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378654764}}
