{"type":"message","id":"e2c945ad","parentId":"d3dabac0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:57:42.734Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q9ic8op6p6y7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 145714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment completed - key finding was that CFI alone loses too much recall\r\n3. Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n4. The formula to test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe last pulse was `pulse_2026-03-24 145617.md` which appended to `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md`.\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to run the hybrid scoring experiment that was designed but not yet executed. The pending action says:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n- Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Extract CFI and frequency data from the existing analysis\r\n2. Calculate hybrid scores\r\n3. Test the hypothesis\r\n\r\nLooking at the files mentioned:\r\n- `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` - the previous experiment\r\n- `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` - just appended\r\n\r\nLet me check what data is available. The synthesis mentioned:\r\n- CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive\r\n- Tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) is true research trajectory\r\n\r\nSo I have the data. I should run the experiment now.\r\n\r\nActually, let me think about what concrete action advances the goal:\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll design a PowerShell script to process token data, calculating hybrid scores and comparing different threshold strategies. The script will extract key metrics, apply the scoring formula, and generate comparative analysis across different token categories.\r\n\r\nThe goal is to empirically test whether the proposed scoring mechanism effectively distinguishes between constant format and research trajectory tokens. By systematically evaluating 200 pulses and splitting data 80/20, I can validate the approach's discriminative power.\r\n\r\nThe experimental design will involve:\r\n- Calculating hybrid scores\r\n- Comparing against binary thresholds\r\n- Analyzing recall and precision across token types\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) was designed but not yet executed. The formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` needs empirical validation against the existing pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and execute a PowerShell experiment script that applies the hybrid scoring formula to analyze token discrimination between constant-format (metaprogramming) vs research-trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C Validation\r\nGenerated: 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nTest hypothesis: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes:\r\n- Constant format (freq≈160, CFI≈1, score≈1.0) → metaprogramming artifact\r\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score>0.4) → true causal content\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- Dataset: 200 pulses from corpus\r\n- Train/Test split: 80/20\r\n- Metric: Precision and recall for research trajectory identification\r\n\r\n## Token Categories (from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md)\r\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Score | Classification |\r\n|-------|------|-----|-------|----------------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\r\n| \"completed at:\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\r\n| \"Phase 0\" | 85 | 0.89 | 0.74 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\r\n| \"CFI\" | 112 | 0.72 | 0.60 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.68 | 0.23 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\r\n\r\n## Scoring Formula\r\n```powershell\r\n$score = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis Test\r\nIf score > 0.4 → classify as research trajectory\r\nExpected result:\r\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1): score=1.0 (BUT these should be manually tagged)\r\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5): score > 0.4 (KEEP)\r\n\r\n## KEY INSIGHT\r\nThe hybrid scoring does NOT filter constant-format tokens (they score high).\r\nThese need a SEPARATE filter: freq >= 150 as \"metaprogramming contamination\".\r\nFinal filter: (score > 0.4) AND (freq < 150)\r\n\"\r\nfile: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:57:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378662732}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbc91d76","parentId":"e2c945ad","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:57:45.884Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md file with the experiment execution results. Let me first get the latest pulse log and then write the updated experiment file.","thinkingSignature":"d94b48dfc47017f0086b6e52a12469c6d34f3ffb28de3327ed7bb349989cf0d8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s8fn4afbnekv_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\research\\CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3371,"output":87,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774378662734}}
{"type":"message","id":"0fc2ec9f","parentId":"bbc91d76","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:57:45.888Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_s8fn4afbnekv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n# Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n\n## Hypothesis\nThe hybrid formula should:\n- De-weight constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.00 → score≈1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0, but freq/120=1.33 capped at 1.0)\n- Properly score research trajectory tokens (freq=60, CFI=0.7 → score=0.7 × 0.5 = 0.35)\n- Better distinguish signal from metaprogramming noise\n\n## Method\n- 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split\n- Strategy A: Binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\n- Strategy C: Hybrid score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n- Metric: Precision, Recall, F1 for identifying \"important\" tokens\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Implement scoring formulas\n- [ ] Run on pulse corpus\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall curves\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378665887}}
{"type":"message","id":"f32f90a2","parentId":"0fc2ec9f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:57:54.546Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now write the updated experiment file with the execution results based on the observation from the pulse.","thinkingSignature":"4d413c88a65240693bd0214457fe546c17a9361d3b5ed6356afa5c2f53ebb483"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l22fgxvgeeoc_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C Validation\nGenerated: 2026-03-24\n\n## Objective\nTest hypothesis: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes:\n- Constant format (freq≈160, CFI≈1, score≈1.0) → metaprogramming artifact\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score>0.4) → true causal content\n\n## Experiment Design\n- Dataset: 200 pulses from corpus\n- Train/Test split: 80/20\n- Metric: Precision and recall for research trajectory identification\n\n## Token Categories (from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md)\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Score | Classification |\n|-------|------|-----|-------|----------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"completed at:\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"Phase 0\" | 85 | 0.89 | 0.74 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"CFI\" | 112 | 0.72 | 0.60 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.68 | 0.23 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n\n## Scoring Formula\n```powershell\n$score = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\n```\n\n## Hypothesis Test\nIf score > 0.4 → classify as research trajectory\nExpected result:\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1): score=1.0 (BUT these need separate filter)\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5): score > 0.4 (KEEP)\n\n## KEY INSIGHT\nThe hybrid scoring does NOT filter constant-format tokens (they score high).\nThese need a SEPARATE filter: freq >= 150 as \"metaprogramming contamination\".\nFinal filter: (score > 0.4) AND (freq < 150)\n\n## Pending\n- [x] Design experiment (2026-03-24)\n- [ ] Implement scoring formulas\n- [ ] Run on pulse corpus\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall curves\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\research\\CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3710,"output":632,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16587,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774378665889}}
